=item C<lpeg.type (value)>

If the given value is a pattern, returns the string C<"pattern">.
Otherwise returns B<nil>.

=cut

.sub 'type'
    .param pmc value :optional
    .param pmc extra :slurpy
    .local pmc res
    $I0 = testpattern(1, value)
